items.fromString:
h3. Context

[~accountid:61c2e7b1567cb700702332ad] came to me and told me that [this GitHub job|https://github.com/smile2impress/backoffice/actions/runs/4497404638/jobs/7912968854] didn’t create a release. I checked the job and found that there was a message in the logs: {{We have a release branch with the same version as a release in live. Please delete release branch.}} 

h3. Proposal

[Here|https://github.com/smile2impress/treatment-monitoring-release-manager-action/blob/857988186dbd5b8e55dc1ea3d98223b948f042ff/src/index.ts#L26-L32] in the Treatment Monitoring Release Manager (TMRM) I see that we just {{console.log}} the problem. I think we have to throw an error.

h3. DoD

* User runs the GitHub action for creating a new minor release (screenshot below)
** TMRM finds that [this condition|https://github.com/smile2impress/treatment-monitoring-release-manager-action/blob/857988186dbd5b8e55dc1ea3d98223b948f042ff/src/index.ts#L26-L32] is true
*** TMRM throws an error
* User runs the GitHub action for creating a new minor release (screenshot below)
** TMRM finds that [this condition|https://github.com/smile2impress/treatment-monitoring-release-manager-action/blob/857988186dbd5b8e55dc1ea3d98223b948f042ff/src/index.ts#L33-L43] is true
*** TMRM throws an error



h3. Materials

Creating a new minor release via GitHub actions:

!Screenshot 2023-03-23 at 10.34.02.png|width=1316,height=465,alt="Creating a new minor release via GitHub actions"!
